            <title>[CASSANDRA-20728] Streaming abort race leaves orphaned partially written sstables on disk</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20728</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As discussed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14554&quot; title=&quot;Streaming needs to synchronise access to LifecycleTransaction&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-14554&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-14554&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; it is possible for streaming to leave half-written sstables around on disk, creating toil on bounces where operators have to delete the files manually.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
